            "answer_text": "Rocks and sticks were the earliest weapons. Techniques developed for sharping sticks and hardening them with fire, chipping rocks into stone axes, blades, and spear heads. A simple hide sling for throwing stones may have been next. The atlatl a notched stick used as an arm-extender to throw a dart or spear, was a very early advance. The bow and arrow was the weapon that reigned supreme for millennia. ",
